quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  7,196,"Surely, my protector is Allah who has revealed the Book and who does protect the righteous.""
  7,197,"And those whom you call beside Him cannot help you, nor can they help themselves."
  7,198,"And if you call them for guidance, they shall not hear. And you see them looking at you while they do not see."
  7,199,"Take to forbearance, and bid the Fair and ignore the ignorant."
  7,200,"And if you are stricken with a strike from the Shaitan, seek refuge with Allah. Surely, He is All-Hearing, All-Knowing."
  7,201,"Surely those who are God-fearing, when they are touched by a visit from Shaitan, they become conscious, and, at once they are watchful."
  7,202,"As for the brethren of Shaitans, the shaitans drag them on into the error, and they do not stop short."
  7,203,"And when you do not bring them a sig "Could you not make up one?" Say, "I only is revealed to me from my Lord." This is insights from your Lord and a guidance and mercy for a people who believe."
  7,204,"And when the Qur'an is recited, listen to it and be silent, so that you may be blessed."
  7,205,"And remember your Lord in yourself with humility and fear, and without speaking loudly, in mornings and evenings, and do not be among the heedless."
  7,206,"Surely, those who are with your Lord are not arrogant against His worship, and they proclaim His purity, and before Him they prostrate."